1.text: Fill a bowl with 1  c (240 mL) of white vinegar.

2.text: Submerge your necklace in the vinegar completely.

3.text: Let your necklace sit for about 8 hours.

4.text: Scrub off the rust with a toothbrush.

5.text: Rinse off your necklace with cool water.

6.text: Pat your necklace dry with a clean cloth.

7.text: Mix 2 drops of dish soap with 1 cup (240 mL) of warm water.

8.text: Rub your necklace in the soap and water with your fingers.

9.text: Rinse your necklace under warm water.

10.text: Pat your necklace dry with a clean cloth.

11.text: Line a small bowl with aluminum foil.

12.text: Mix 1 tbsp (14 g) of baking soda and 1 tbsp (14 g) of table salt with warm water.

13.text: Submerge your necklace in the mixture and make sure it touches the foil.

14.text: Let the necklace sit for 2 to 10 minutes.

15.text: Rinse your necklace with cold water.

16.text: Pat the necklace dry with a clean cloth.
